-- DIMENSION 4: Data Sovereignty (Questions 18-23)
(18, 4, 'Data Sovereignty', 'Does your nation have enforceable data residency requirements for strategic and citizen data?', 'No data localisation requirements', 'Data localisation laws exist but enforcement is limited', 'Data localisation with enforcement for strategic/government data', 'Comprehensive data residency framework with enforcement across public and private sectors', 10, 35, 65, 90),
(19, 4, 'Data Sovereignty', 'What proportion of government cloud workloads run on sovereign or sovereignty-graded infrastructure?', 'Most government cloud workloads on commercial foreign cloud', 'Some workloads on sovereign-graded cloud but majority on foreign', 'Majority of government cloud on sovereign/domestic infrastructure', 'All sensitive government workloads on sovereign cloud with air-gap capability', 15, 40, 70, 95),
