(27, 5, 'Directed Intelligence Maturity', 'Can you attribute specific, documented outcomes to your AI deployments?', 'No formal outcome measurement for AI deployments', 'Anecdotal outcomes reported but not systematically measured', 'Some AI deployments have documented, measured outcomes', 'Systematic outcome attribution: all production AI systems have documented, measured impact', 5, 25, 55, 90),
(28, 5, 'Directed Intelligence Maturity', 'Does your government have defined human-agent decision ratios and override mechanisms?', 'No human-agent governance framework exists', 'General AI ethics principles but no operational human-agent rules', 'Human-agent decision policies defined for some departments', 'Comprehensive framework: human-agent ratios, override mechanisms, and accountability per department', 5, 25, 55, 90),
(29, 5, 'Directed Intelligence Maturity', 'Have your AI programmes survived at least one leadership change, budget cycle, or political transition?', 'AI programmes are too new to have faced a transition', 'AI programmes exist but have been disrupted by leadership or budget changes', 'Core AI programmes survived one transition with some continuity', 'AI programmes have institutional durability: survived multiple transitions with documented continuity', 20, 30, 60, 90),
(30, 5, 'Directed Intelligence Maturity', 'Does your nation have a sovereign AI model development programme with published roadmaps and verifiable milestones?', 'No sovereign AI model development programme exists', 'Initial discussions or exploratory studies only', 'Programme exists but lacks funding or clear milestones', 'Fully funded sovereign AI model programme with published roadmap and verifiable milestones', 10, 30, 60, 95);

